= SDL_GetThreadName =
Use this function to get the thread name as it was specified in [[SDL_CreateThread]]().


== Syntax ==
```c++
const char* SDL_GetThreadName(SDL_Thread* thread)
```

== Function Parameters ==
{|
|'''thread'''
|the thread to query
|}

== Return Value ==
Returns a pointer to a UTF-8 string that names the specified thread, or NULL if it doesn't have a name,,; call [[SDL_GetError]]() for more information,,.

